text: Appetizers were great! Entrees were good. BE WARNED of the 'sampler' appetizer. We had a party of about 10 and were waiting for everyone to arrive. Our waiter offered to bring out a sampling of appetizers for 5 of us to nibble on while we waited. The 'sampling' ended up to be two full orders of each appetizer on the menu and cost more than $150 off the bat. Do not be fooled by waiters who want to increase their check size aka their tip.  We were disappointed in the deceit and will not return.

text: Been there twice, first with co-workers and later, with family.  Tasty new take on tacos!  Faves were the Gio taco with pork belly and the surprisingly crispy Chipper Fish taco with the yucca chips on top. He told her she was worthless and that she needed makeup.  This had to be one of the most beautiful women I have ever seen. text: I'm not going to rate this place yet on 1 visit. The patio was cool and I imagine a great place to watch the game! Or to pre drink and to take the shuttle to the game. I love that!  My wings and ribs were really good and I would order this again.  However, coleslaw is very important with bbq! It was soggy, extremely salty and room temperate. I could not eat it. Coleslaw is so cheap to make, I suggest making it maybe daily or more often and serve cold.  (Maybe it was warm because of a heat lamp?)

text:
I have been by this place in my car and walking past on the sidewalk more times than I count. Never went in because I assumed it was a smoke-filled dive bar.

First visit tonight to try it out because we heard the bbq was very good, plus just wanted to watch the Cards game.

I was pleasantly surprised.  Tons of flat screens and the place is really clean.  To top it off, the bbq is amazing!  And the smoky, bbq smells permeate the air, adding to the atmosphere.

I will absolutely come back here!
